      "message": "My expectation was that a subattr would describe a subset of a parent group, whereas cellular_esim would be a separate group, similar to wificell vs wificell_roam.\n\ni.e. we would create separate cellular_ota_esim{_unstable} control files, which would use:\n  test_exprs\u003d[\u0027(\"group:cellular_esim\" \u0026\u0026 {!}cellular_stable)\u0027]\n\nWhereas if we make this a subattr, wouldn\u0027t we need to explicitly exclude esim in any non esim control files? i.e. wouldn\u0027t the current control file filter include the esim tests:\n  test_exprs\u003d[\u0027(\"group:cellular\" \u0026\u0026 {!}cellular_stable)\u0027]\n\nUnless we changed all of those to:\n  test_exprs\u003d[\u0027(\"group:cellular_esim\" \u0026\u0026 !cellular_esim \u0026\u0026{!}cellular_stable)\u0027]\n\n?",
